  "prompt": "What are some ethical dilemmas?",
  "response": "Here are some classic ethical dilemmas:\n\n1. Trolley Problem\n- A trolley is heading toward 5 people\n- You can divert it to kill 1 person instead\n- Whether to actively choose to cause one death to save more\n\n2. Organ Donation Scenario\n- One patient needs multiple organs to survive\n- Another patient could be killed to harvest those organs\n- Whether sacrificing one life could save multiple lives\n\n3. Whistleblowing\n- Knowing about unethical/illegal practices at work\n- Reporting could cost you your job\n- Staying silent means allowing potential harm to continue\n\n4. Euthanasia\n- Helping someone with terminal illness end their suffering\n- Balancing personal autonomy with sanctity of life\n\n5. Privacy vs Public Safety\n- Knowing private information that might prevent a potential crime\n- Weighing individual privacy rights against potential harm prevention\n\n6. Resource Allocation\n- Limited medical resources\n- Choosing who receives treatment when not everyone can be saved\n\n7. AI and Autonomous Vehicle Decisions\n- Programming self-driving cars to make split-second moral choices\n- Deciding whom to prioritize in unavoidable accident scenarios\n\nThese dilemmas often involve competing moral principles and no clear \"right\" answer.",
